<sect2 id="gimp-filter-tile-seamless">
  <title>Tile Seamless</title>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Filters</primary>
    <secondary>Map</secondary>
    <tertiary>Tile Seamless</tertiary>
  </indexterm>
  <indexterm>
    <primary>Tile Seamless</primary>
  </indexterm>
  <sect3>
    <title>Overview</title>
    <figure>
      <title>An example of Tile Seamless.</title>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="JPG"
            fileref="images/filters/examples/taj_orig.jpg"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Original</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata format="JPG"
            fileref="images/filters/examples/map-taj-seamless.jpg"/>
        </imageobject>
        <caption>
          <para>Tile Seamless applied</para>
        </caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </figure>
    <para>
      This filter modifies the image for tiling by creating seamless edges.
      Such an image can be used as a pattern for a web-page. This filter has
      no option, and result may need correction.
    </para>
  </sect3>

